summer jobs dupont pioneer relies on our seasonal employees to sustain our efforts in seed production . we offer a variety of summer jobs , including internships , detasseling , detasseling crew leaders , seed field inspecting , pollinating , data collection and field research . seasonal employees will gain experience during the summer while benefiting from the financial rewards . pollinators pollination is the transfer of pollen from the male part of the corn plant ( tassel ) to the female part ( silk ) . there are two types : cross-pollination - occurs when pollen from one corn plant transfers to the silk of another corn plant . self-pollination - occurs when pollen from one corn plant transfers to the silk of the same corn plant . our pollinators work to ensure that the right corn is crossed at just the right time . be prepared for a tough work_environment that may be hot , humid and muddy . pollinating usually starts in mid-july and lasts from 10 days to three weeks , consecutively . the work day starts in the field at approximately 7 : 30 am and ends at 4 pm but , the schedule ultimately depends on the weather and peak periods of development . during pollinating season , work is performed seven days a week-rain or shine-which means you may be working saturday and / or sunday . safety safety is dupont pioneer 's number_one priority . failure to adhere to all safety policies and procedures could lead to disciplinary action , including termination of employment . pioneer will provide personal protective equipment ( ppe ) such as eye protection and gloves , which are required for safety reasons . you must be at least 15 years old . apply at : pioneer hi-bred int'l , inc . 150 air links dr no phone_calls please . pick_up applications between 8am-12pm and 1pm-4 . 30pm monday -
